radare (1:1.4.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release
  * radare-gtk suggests graphviz, which is used by agdv command
  * remove valac and libvala-dev build dependency; we don't need
    a devel build.
  * Bashisms have been fixed upstream (Closes: #535884)
  * Fix segfault appearing when compiling with -O2 on i386 (Closes: #534700)
  * Update Debian Standard Version to 3.8.2
  * Split radare-common into the following packages:
   - radare-common       scripts and tools of the radare toolchain
   - radare-lua          lua bindings for radare
   - radare-perl         perl bindings for radare
   - radare-python       python bindings for radare
  * Remove Readme.Debian, i386 segfault should be fixed

 -- Sebastian Reichel <elektranox@gmail.com>  Wed, 27 Jun 2009 00:03:50 +0200

